Project Name: East Asian Maps in the Bruman Collection
Title: East Asian Maps in the Bruman Collection
Description.fundingNote: Access to this collection is generously supported by Sammy Yukuan Lee Foundation.
Description.note: The East Asian Maps Collection consists of 1079 maps of China, Japan, Korea, Manchuria, and other areas in East Asia. The maps were produced between 1800 and 1960s. A majority of them produced by the Office of Strategic Service, the American Map Society, the National Geographic Magazine, and government agents or commercial publishers in China, Great Britain, and Japan. Some of the maps were once highly classified and produced in limited quantities.
